<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-6723] Type checking generic types on static methods incorrectly fails for trivial cases</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6723</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;Type checking for generic method type parameters does not work when calling from a static method to another static method for trivially simple cases.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See the following gist:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/mperry/11285137&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gist.github.com/mperry/11285137&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suspect this has gotten worse from 2.2.2 to 2.3.0-rc-1 as my project, FunctionalGroovy, does this a lot and I now have many compilation issues related to this when previous I did not.  A small number of these are genuine type checking issues.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
